FBIS3-39652 "drweu034_q_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 TURKEY Foreign Ministry: Greek Decision on Macedonia `Unjust' TA1702163394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1615 GMT 17 Feb 94 TA1702163394 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ankara, Feb 17 (A.A) -- Turkey on Thursday [17 February] expressed concern over Greek decision taken toward Macedonia to impose sanctions on this country. Foreign Ministry officials said "Turkey believed that Greek decision taken toward Macedonian Republic was unjust." Officials said the decision was taken when the Balkans needed peace, stability, and cooperation. It went on saying that the decision recalled "Cold War" period. Greece said on Wednesday it was stopping The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia from using the Greek port of Thessaloniki for its supplies, except for humanitarian aid.
